## 🚫 NEVER DO

1. ❌ Push config without live terminal display
2. ❌ Delete config without live terminal display
3. ❌ Hardcode values without detection chain
4. ❌ Assume interface types (PWHE vs L2-AC)
5. ❌ Use simplified text in config previews
6. ❌ Forget `rollback 0` before terminal paste
7. ❌ Skip time estimation
8. ❌ Implement for single-device only
9. ❌ Generate invalid DNOS syntax
10. ❌ Silent operations without user feedback
11. ❌ Skip WAN interfaces in VLAN modifications
12. ❌ Delete services without offering to delete attached interfaces
13. ❌ Create menus/prompts without [B] Back option
14. ❌ Trap user in a flow without escape route
15. ❌ Lose user-entered values when going back

---

## ✅ ALWAYS DO

1. ✅ Read existing code before modifying
2. ✅ Validate DNOS syntax against running configs
3. ✅ Show live terminal for ALL pushes AND deletes
4. ✅ Offer all 3 push methods
5. ✅ Estimate time before, save timing after
6. ✅ Implement for both single and multi-device
7. ✅ Use ThreadPoolExecutor for parallel ops
8. ✅ Detect values from config before using defaults
9. ✅ Update all similar UI elements when changing format
10. ✅ Test thoroughly before considering complete
11. ✅ Detect and show attached interfaces when deleting services
12. ✅ Use wider panels (70 chars) with 8+ terminal lines
13. ✅ Include [B] Back option in EVERY menu and prompt
14. ✅ Allow user to reconfigure any entered value
15. ✅ Preserve user inputs in state when navigating back

